                <h3 class="title">Bloomberg on when a computer should replace a journalist</h3>
                <p class="dek">
                                            "Where there's no intellectual content added by the reporter," says media mogul Michael Bloomberg, "you can have the computer do it. We want the ...
                                    </p>
            </figcaption></figure></a>
</div><p>Michael Bloomberg: These people are doing one-minute radio business updates for a hundred different radio stations around the country. </p><p>But the real money and most of the profits come from a mysterious piece of equipment known as the Bloomberg Terminal that sits on the desks of titans and traders all over the world. </p><p>Michael Bloomberg: Sound, pictures, graphics, tabular data. Different ways to look at the markets.</p><div class="shortcode-gallery shortcode large left" id="shortcode-video" data-ads='{"extraWordCount":50}'>
    <a id="relatedVideoContainer" data-open="modalAsync" data-modal-async-url="/videos/4f667293-7600-4e7b-bca4-76126aad2d71/xhr" data-modal-options='{"position": "absolute", "checkIE": "true"}' data-omniture-track="trackVideoOverlayView" data-omniture-track-data='{"siteSection":"60 Minutes: Segment Extras","siteHier":["60 Minutes: Segment Extras","60 Minutes"],"pageType":"video","mediaTitle":"Two things Bloomberg says he\u0027s no good at, right now","mediaId":"4f667293-7600-4e7b-bca4-76126aad2d71","mediaType":"content_video","topicId":["7ee6e32c-352e-11e3-8ce8-047d7b15b92e"],"topicName":["60 Minutes: Segment Extras"]}' href="/videos/two-things-bloomberg-says-hes-no-good-at-right-now">
